<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   RPF Says Government Threatening More Massacres </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Says Government Threatening More Massacres </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1905155694 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in French to 
Rwanda 1030 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1905155694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The genocide continues at a greater pace than ever. 
Putting aside Mr. Theodore Sindikubwabo's pleasure over the 
extermination of Tutsis in Kibuye and Cyangugu, government 
forces recently threatened that they would massacre those 
refugees in the Hotel Des Milles Collines, as well as several 
orphans which were taken hostage by government soldiers and 
Interahamwe [Republican National Movement for Democracy and 
Development militias]. The Interahamwe militiamen and 
government troops are ready to massacre all these people if the 
Rwandan Patriotic Front continues its military advance. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

