<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Conducts `Minor' Cabinet Reshuffle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2005102594 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 
1700 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2005102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ali Hassan Mwinyi has carried out a minor 
cabinet reshuffle. He has appointed a junior minister, two new 
regional commissioners, changed the jobs of two regional 
commissioners, and transferred one regional commissioner. 
  A State House statement said Mtwara Regional Commissioner 
Sylvia Kate Kamba has been appointed deputy minister in the 
Ministry of Social Development, Women, and Children. National 
Planning Commission Commissioner Nsa Kaisi has been appointed 
the new regional commissioner of Mtwara region to succeed Kate 
Kamba. President Mwinyi has also appointed Mahange MP, Gibson 
Itatiro, as the new regional commissioner of Morogoro Region 
replacing Yusuf Makamba, who has been transferred to Kigoma 
Region to replace Sebastian Kinyondo who has been appointed 
national commissioner of planning. Mr. Kinyondo replaces Pius 
Msekwa who was recently elected speaker of the Union Parliament. 
The statement said the changes will take effect immediately. 

</TEXT>

