BFN 

  [Text] Mrs. Musuleng-Cooper is to be inducted today as 
foreign minister. Mrs. Cooper was yesterday confirmed by the 
Transitional Legislative Assembly following confirmation 
hearings at the Capitol. 
  Speaking during the hearing, Mrs. Cooper expressed her 
desire 
to work closely with all friendly nations for the speedy 
restoration of general peace to this country. She said a lot is 
required from the outside world for the furtherance of peace and 
reconciliation. She stressed the need for proper coordination 
and consultation between the transitional government and the 
international community and build a vibrant nation through free 
and fair democratic elections. 
  Mrs. Cooper pledged not to disrupt the existing operations 
of 
the Foreign Ministry but to improve working conditions of the 
staff so that we can effectively strengthen the relationship 
between Liberia and the world community. 

