<F P=102>   AB1905152594 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1200 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1905152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Problems slowing down the implementation of the 
Cotonou peace agreement for Liberia have been the key elements 
of lengthy discussions between the former NPRA [National 
Patriotic Reconstruction Assembly] government's President 
Charles Gankay Taylor and UN's special representative to 
Liberia, Mr. Trevor Gordon-Somers. The meeting is believed to 
have centered on removing obstacles in the way of the peace 
process. Inside sources said one of the highlights of the 
meeting was the slow pace of the deployment of the expanded 
ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire 
Monitoring Group] throughout Liberia which is a prerequisite to 
the disarmament exercise of all fighting groups in the country. 
This has been the hurdle in carrying out the military aspect of 
the Cotonou accord. 

</TEXT>

