GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2005084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos NTA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Anambra State police command has discovered an 
illegal arms factory at Ntede in Oyi local government area of 
the state. Correspondent Eddy Okafor reports that the 
proprietor of the factory was arrested following information 
given by two armed robbery suspects: 
  [Begin Okafor recording] Arraigning the illegal arms 
manufacturer in Government House, Oka, the state police 
commissioner, Alhaji Mamman Ankah, said two shotguns, one 
locally made pistol, and 12 live cartridges were recovered from 
the factory. Speaking while inspecting the arms and ammunition, 
the state administrator, Kuman Nakata, said he is not opposed to 
possession of arms for security purposes, provided such 
possession is within the provisions of the law. He directed the 
police to carry out thorough investigations with a view to 
detecting similar factories elsewhere. 
  Earlier, the arrested arms manufacturer said he got his 
license to manufacture arms from colonial masters in 1952, 
adding that most of the guns recovered belong to vigilante 
groups from neighboring towns. Meanwhile, the two teenage 
robbery suspects who gave the tipoff after the arrest [words 
indistinct] confessed robbing a man of the sum of 1,500 naira. 
The state commissioner of police, Alhaji Mamman, told NTA News 
of the determination of his command to rid the state of 
criminals. He said the suspects would soon appear in court. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

