<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] N'Dalatando is facing a critical situation. The 
Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola [MPLA] is bent on 
decimating the residents of N'Dalatando, using its air force and 
long-range artillery pieces. 
  About 28 air raids were carried out on 18 May. The MPLA used 
TC- 7's, MiG-23's, and Su's. More than 70 bombs with substances 
banned internationally were being dropped on the city and 
outlaying areas daily. [passage omitted] 
  A terrible MPLA military offensive is under way in Cuanza 
Sul. The four-pronged offensive was launched from Waku-Kungo and 
Gabela and is designed to capture the District of Ebo. The 
offensive, which began on 16 May 1994, has been characterized by 
massive air force attacks and artillery shelling. Violent 
clashes have been taking place with the UNITA [National Union 
for the Total Independence of Angola] armed forces defending the 
people from the MPLA adventure. People's Armed Forces for the 
Liberation of Angola [FAPLA] units have been left to their own 
devices. A number of FAPLA members have surrendered to UNITA. 
Cadet Officer Daniel Caieba, a native of (Cassongue), 
surrendered to UNITA on 17 May. [passage omitted] 
  The communist regime of Jose Eduardo dos Santos is bent on 
resuming war in the city of Bie. Lethal equipment for MPLA 
troops was unloaded in Bie at approximately 0625 on 18 May. 
Flying from Luanda, a IL-776 military aircraft dropped eight 
parachutes, but all of them fell in the sector of the city 
controlled by UNITA. Five parachutes had grenades, large 
quantities of AK-47's, AGS 17 ammunition belts, and AK-47 
ammunition boxes. The other three parachutes had Racal-30 
communications radios. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

