<H3> <TI>   No Talks Held in Lusaka at UNITA's Request </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Talks Held in Lusaka at UNITA's Request </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1905202594 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1905202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Lusaka by correspondent Manuel da Conceicao] </F>
  [Text] There were no talks in Lusaka today. The UNITA 
[National Union for the Total Independence of Angola] 
negotiating team this morning informed its government 
counterpart that it was not able to take part in the talks 
because the UNITA leader had not given the green light to the 
issues raised by the UNITA negotiators about Vorgan [Voice of 
Resistance of the Black Cockerel]. The government accepted the 
UNITA negotiators' request for an adjournment because that is 
the prerogative of the two teams. There are decisions that the 
two negotiating teams cannot make without consulting their 
leaders. 
  Today the two delegations held separate meetings. A 
well-placed UNITA source said in Lusaka today that the issues 
raised with Jonas Savimbi are not only linked to Vorgan, but 
also to the government's reaction to UNITA's participation at 
various levels of government. UNITA says the (?government's 
reaction) has been negative. There is nothing scheduled for 
tomorrow. It all depends on UNITA. Meanwhile, the government 
continues to wait patiently. 

</TEXT>

