<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The political crisis in Lesotho has deepened after a 
meeting of leaders failed to end the police and prison guards' 
strike. Reports say the main opposition party walked out of the 
emergency talks after being accused by Prime Minister Ntsu 
Mokhehle of complicity in the strike. About 2,500 policemen 
below the rank of captain in the country's 3,000-strong police 
force started striking last week demanding a 60 percent pay 
increase. They were joined by junior prison guards. 

</TEXT>

