  [Text] Gilberto Katema, political representative of the 
Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] in Cabo Delgado 
Province, has once again accused Frelimo [Mozambique Liberation 
Front] and the government of intimidating members of his 
organization and the people in general for showing support for 
Afonso Dhlakama's organization. He said threats have been made 
with firearms and bladed weapons. Gilberto Katema mentioned 
cases of Renamo delegates who were assaulted in Meluco and 
Macomia, and of threats of assault reported at the Mueda 
highlands. 

