<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government yesterday demobilized 1,036 soldiers. 
This represents a record number of soldiers demobilized in a 
single day since the start of the operation. Yesterday Renamo 
[Mozambique National Resistance] demobilized 172 troops. A 
total of 16,879 government and Renamo soldiers have already been 
demobilized, of which 16,041 are from the government and the 
remainder from Renamo. 

