<H3> <TI>   National TV To Introduce Pay Channel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National TV To Introduce Pay Channel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2005092194 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 1800 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2005092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation [ZNBC] 
acting director general Mr. Dunken Mbazima has confirmed that 
ZNBC is to introduce a pay channel on television. Mr. Mbazima 
said he has received many queries today about the pay channel 
following the announcement published in today's TIMES OF ZAMBIA 
by the minister of information of broadcasting and services, Mr. 
Keli Walubita. The government has already approved the project 
and other formalities are now being worked out. Mr. Mbazima 
said ZNBC has been strapped for cash and this venture is 
expected to improve the corporation's financial standing. 
Viewers who will subscribe to the channel in areas outside 
Lusaka, the Copperbelt, and Livingstone transmitter coverage 
range will be serviced through the cellular network. 

</TEXT>

