<H3> <TI>   Senate President Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate President Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2005090694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0852 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2005090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Parliament May 20 SAPA -- Former justice and defence 
ministers Mr Kobie Coetsee was unanimously elected president of 
the Senate on Friday. Mr Govan Archibald Mbeki, former Robben 
Island prisoner released in 1987, was unanimously elected 
deputy-president of the Senate on Friday. 

</TEXT>

