<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments on ANC Development Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on ANC Development Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2005091694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2005091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy President F.W. de Klerk has played down 
concern that the ANC's reconstruction and development plan will 
cost twice as much as originally estimated. Addressing a news 
conference in London he said that the government would provide a 
better quality of life for everyone, but only by spending what 
it could afford. This might mean that the government would not 
reach the ANC's declared goal of one million new homes in five 
years. He said South Africa was not looking for handouts but 
for free trade and investment. Mr. De Klerk is in London to 
deliver the SUNDAY TIMES Nobel Laureate peace lecture. 

</TEXT>

