<H3> <TI>   Public Servants Group Warns of `Unrest' Over Pay Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Public Servants Group Warns of `Unrest' Over Pay Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2005092794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2005092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Public Servants Association of South Africa has 
warned that serious unrest could result from the nonpayment of 
special danger allowances promised to Correctional Services 
personnel over the election period. The newly-appointed general 
manager of the association, Mr. Casper van Rensburg, said the 
association would take all the necessary steps to ensure that 
its Correctional Services members were paid the special 
allowance which was granted to other uniformed personnel. 

</TEXT>

