<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Troops Attack Convoy; More Than 20 Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA Troops Attack Convoy; More Than 20 Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1905111494 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1905111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Troops belonging to the National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] ambushed a five-vehicle 
convoy belonging to civilians. They murdered more than 20 
people in the attack, which took place between Porto Amboim and 
Luanda. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

