<H3> <TI>   New 90-Member Senate Meets for First Time </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New 90-Member Senate Meets for First Time </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2005081894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0805 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2005081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Parliament May 20 SAPA -- South Africa's new 
90-member Senate met for the first time on Friday at 10AM in the 
historic old senate chamber at Parliament. Chief Justice 
Michael Corbett constituted it and started swearing in its 
members. 
  One of the Senate's main functions will be to form the 
Constitutional Assembly with the 400 members of the National 
Assembly to write South Africa's final constitution. It will 
also be able to initiate legislation. 

</TEXT>

