<H3> <TI>   CAR Lifts Ban on Participating in Parliamentary Sessions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CAR Lifts Ban on Participating in Parliamentary Sessions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2005134794 Lome Radio Lome in French 1230 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2005134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by Yaovi Agboyibor, chairman of the Action </F>
Committee for Renewal in Lome on 20 May] 
  [Text] The steering committee of the Action Committee for 
Renewal [CAR] met today and took note of the fact that the 
so-called by-elections slated for 15 May did not take place. 
The CAR interprets the nonorganization of these elections as 
the government's recognition of the fact that these elections 
can only take place at a date when the conditions of legality, 
openness, and security have been met. Consequently, the CAR has 
decided to lift its ban on the participation of its deputies in 
National Assembly sessions. 

</TEXT>

