<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Plane Crashes; Several `Feared' Dead </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2105182894 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2105182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A plane belonging to the Tanzania Peoples' Defense 
Forces, TPDF, crashed shortly before landing at the Bukoba 
airport. The Tanzania news agency, SHIHATA, said several people 
are feared dead in the accident which occurred about 1300 hours 
today. The Buffalo plane, registration number JWY 902, was on a 
scheduled Dar es Salaam-Mwanza-Tabora flight. SHIHATA quoted 
eyewitnesses as saying that one of the wings of the aircraft hit 
a tree as it was approaching the airport before it crashed into 
a house bursting into flames. The house used as a clinic also 
caught fire. Survivors say that the plane was also carrying two 
coffins scheduled for burial at Bukoba and Tabora respectively. 

</TEXT>

