<H3> <TI>   Government Aircraft Reportedly Bomb N'Dalatando </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Aircraft Reportedly Bomb N'Dalatando </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2105074794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2105074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The residents of N'Dalatando, capital of Cuanza 
Norte Province, are still crying for their beloved relatives who 
are being killed daily by Engineer Jose Eduardo dos Santos' 
criminal aircraft. Reports from Firmino Lukamba, Voice of 
Resistance of the Black Cockerel's correspondent in that city, 
say that people are crying everywhere. 
  Yet another father, a mother, a grandfather, or son dies. 
Yesterday the Popular Movement for the Liberation of 
Angola-Labor Party [MPLA-PT] aircraft once again carried out 
another heavy air raid against positions on the outskirts of 
N'Dalatando. The raids were carried out by 3 Su-25 aircraft and 
5 PC-7 aircraft which dropped highly potent toxic bombs over 
villages, districts, and communes, resulting in considerable 
human and material losses. Firmino Lukamba says that the 
democratic world should persuade Luanda to stop such operations. 
He said that there is authentic genocide in N'Dalatando, and 
the international community is silent about the issue. 

</TEXT>

