<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Red Cross Reports `Hundreds of Thousands' of New Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Red Cross Reports `Hundreds of Thousands' of New Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005170294 Paris AFP in English 1644 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2005170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, May 20 (AFP) -- Hundreds of thousands of 
people are fleeing central Rwanda as heavy fighting in the 
capital Kigali and elsewhere in the central African nation 
causes a new exodus of refugees, an International Committee of 
the Red Cross [ICRC] spokesman said Friday. 
  The ICRC appealed for UN peacekeepers to be sent in as 
quickly as possible and for the establishment of humanitarian 
corridors through the country. 
  Up to half a million Rwandans are believed to have died in 
ethnic and political killings between members of the Hutu and 
Tutsi people that broke out in early April. 

</TEXT>

