<F P=106> [Report from Lusaka by correspondent Alves Antonio] </F>
  [Text] Members of the UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] delegation to the peace talks have 
already left Lusaka for Huambo. On board the UN aircraft that 
took off from the Lusaka International Airport at about 1500 on 
20 May were Eugenio Manuvakola, Jorge Valentim, Isaias Samakuva, 
and others. Only Joao Vaikene and (Evaristo) Oliveira stayed 
behind. The talks are scheduled to resume either on 24 or 25 
May. 

