<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Issues Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Issues Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2105205494 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2105205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Government of the Republic of </F>
Angola on 21 May] 
  [Text] The Government of the Republic of Angola strongly 
condemns the actions carried out by the National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] against the World Food 
Program [WFP] planes rendering humanitarian assistance to the 
victims of war and other disasters. The government feels that 
the actions against WFP planes in the city of Malange on 16, 18, 
19, and 20 May, forcing the WFP to suspend humanitarian 
assistance to Malange residents, constitute a flagrant violation 
of UNITA's pledge regarding the distribution of humanitarian 
assistance to all needy Angolan people, regardless of the area 
where they are found. 
  The government would also like to inform the national and 
international communities about the raids carried out by UNITA 
armed elements against the warehouses of international 
nongovernmental organizations in the provinces of Uige and 
Huambo. It also condemns the diversion of goods destined to the 
needy for military purposes. 
  In view of this unfavorable picture created by UNITA, the 
Government of the Republic of Angola has decided to temporarily 
suspend the WFP and international nongovernmental organizations' 
flights to the provinces of Huambo and Uige until the United 
Nations is able to inform the Government of the Republic of 
Angola that conditions have been reestablished for the 
continuation of humanitarian flights in conditions of security. 
  The government would once again like to call on the 
international community to exercise pressure on UNITA to respect 
the principles of humanitarian assistance and not use this 
assistance for other purposes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

