<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dispute Brewing Over Capital of KwaZulu/Natal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dispute Brewing Over Capital of KwaZulu/Natal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2205104894 Johannesburg SUNDAY TIMES in English 22 May 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MB2205104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SUNDAY TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Carmel Rickard] </F>
  [Text] Deciding on a capital of KwaZulu Natal has the 
potential to become one of the most bitter wrangles in the power 
struggle between the IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] and ANC in the 
province. Ulundi, Durban and Maritzburg are being considered. 
  Premier Frank Mdlalose says the members of the provincial 
legislature should decide the issue -- but his decision to hold 
the next cabinet meeting in Ulundi has been interpreted as 
indicating his own preference. 
  ANC officials have objected to Ulundi, saying they would not 
be safe there. ANC provincial cabinet minister S'bu Ndebele 
said it would not make sense to travel for six hours to attend 
cabinet meetings in Ulundi. 
  The notorious road and bad phone connections are further 
obstacles to making Ulundi the capital, say critics. 

</TEXT>

