<H3> <TI>   Mandela, Makwetu Discuss PAC Integration Into SANDF </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mandela, Makwetu Discuss PAC Integration Into SANDF </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2205201594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1929 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2205201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town May 22 SAPA -- President Nelson Mandela on 
Sunday night held discussions with a Pan Africanist Congress 
[PAC] delegation led by PAC leader Mr Clarence Makwetu on the 
integration of the PAC's armed formation into the South African 
National Defence Force [SANDF]. 
  The newly-appointed chief director of communications in Mr 
Mandela's office, Mr Joel Netshitenzhe, said the PAC was 
interested in participation in an integrated defence force and 
the ANC in principle agreed that the relevant legislation should 
be examined. 
  Defence Minister Mr Joe Modise had been part of Mr Mandela's 
delegation at Sunday night's talks, and Mrs Patricia de Lille 
part of Mr Makwetu's. 
  Mr Netshitenzhe said talks between Mr Mandela and Home 
Affairs Minister Dr Mangosuthu Buthelezi about the controversial 
KwaZulu land deal would possibly not take place on Sunday night, 
but on Monday morning before the Cabinet meeting. 

