<H3> <TI>   NW Minister on AWB Activities, Land Confiscation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NW Minister on AWB Activities, Land Confiscation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2105171994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1632 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2105171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mmabatho May 21 SAPA -- North West Executive 
Commitee member Rocky Malebana Metsing said on Saturday his 
administration would not hesitate to confiscate land, without 
compensation, from farmers who allowed AWB [Afrikaner 
Weerstandsbeweging; Afrikaner Resistance Movement] activities on 
their farms, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio 
news reports. 
  Addressing a meeting at Bapong near Brits on Saturday Mr 
Metsing, whose portfolio is agriculture, said the government 
would not allow farm land to be used for storing weapons or for 
training members of the Afrikaner Weerstandsbeweging's military 
wing. 
  Referring to people who were forceably removed from their 
land under apartheid laws, he said the state would do all in its 
power to ensure they got their land back. 

