<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] South Africans have been advised not to visit 
Lesotho, or to be careful if they do. The South African 
ambassador to Lesotho, Mr. Gerhard Fisser, said the situation in 
the country was tense because of the strike by policemen. He 
confirmed that the country's information minister, Mr. Mpho 
Malie, had been abducted in Maseru. Reports say he was abducted 
by striking policemen. Mr. Fisser said Lesotho's mining 
minister, Mr. Monyane Moleleki, had fled the country, but said 
it was not clear whether he was in South Africa or Botswana. 

