  [Text] Since 0600 this morning, the Rwanda Patriotic Front 
[RPF] has begun observing a two-day truce. This is being done 
to enable the UN special envoy, who is in our country, to hold 
discussions with both sides concerning the UN mission to be 
deployed here. It is within the framework of facilitating this 
mission that the RPF has declared a total truce. The RPF is in 
favor of the truce, but the RPF's observance depends on its 
observance by the Rwandan Army. 

