<H3> <TI>   Rwanda Refugees Returning From Burundi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rwanda Refugees Returning From Burundi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2405162394 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1100 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2405162394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rwandese, who had fled to neighboring Burundi, are 
now coming back in RPF-held areas of Bugesera. The returnees 
are coming from camps in Burundi at Kirundo, (Kiyonza), [word 
indistinct] and Ngozi. More than 2,000 people are reported to 
have come back in the last two days. 

</TEXT>

