  [Text] The foreign ministry today stated that Ethiopia has 
accepted the request of the UN to send her troops to Rwanda. 
Ethiopia accepted the request in accordance with the UN Security 
Council's resolution No. 918 on 17th May 1994, asking all member 
states to send troops toward the UN peacekeeping force in 
Rwanda, which was passed to Ethiopia through the secretary 
general of the organization. The ministry of foreign affairs 
added that Ethiopia has acknowledged her acceptance of the 
request in a letter written to Mr. Butrus-Butrus Ghali dated 
20th May 1994. 

