<H3> <TI>   Cuito Reportedly Under UNITA `Intense Fire' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuito Reportedly Under UNITA `Intense Fire' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2705125394 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2705125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Abel Abraao in Cuito] </F>
  [Text] As we file this report, the city of Cuito is under 
intense fire. Several people have been killed and others 
wounded. We are unable to give the number of victims because of 
the intensity of clashes and shelling. Yet, it is known between 
last night and dawn today, National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola rebels had already fired more than 300 
shells of various caliber at the martyred city. As usual, the 
civil defense, the National Police, and the Angolan Armed Forces 
have halted the destructive wrath of the men from Jamba. We 
expect to give other details in our next report. 

</TEXT>

