BFN 

  [Text] The president of the Republic, Pascal Lissouba, 
returned to Brazzaville shortly before 1500 at the end of an 
African and Asian visit that lasted 17 days. This is the 
longest foreign visit by President Lissouba since he assumed 
power on 31 August 1992. President Lissouba visited South 
Africa, Kenya, Thailand, the PRC, and Ethiopia where he attended 
activities marking the 31st OAU anniversary. 

