<H3> <TI>   New National Development Party Registers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New National Development Party Registers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2605223094 Nairobi KNA in English 1440 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA2605223094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nairobi, 26 May (KNA) -- A new political party, the 
National Development Party (NDP), has been registered, KNA has 
established. 
  According to its certificate of registration, the NDP is led 
by an economist Mr. Stephen Omondi Oludhe as chairman, Mr. David 
Obilo, a teacher as secretary, and a businessman Lucas Okuma as 
treasurer. 
  The registration of the party, under Licence No. 16177 of 6 
May 1994, brings to 10 the number of parties registered in Kenya 
since 1992. 

